description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FREEMAN HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DIRECTORATE OF CARDIOTHORACIC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOCUM CONSULTANT IN RESPIRATORY MEDICINE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REF. 317-LCON-20-261&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to be able to offer an opportunity for a consultant individual to join our well integrated team as a locum for 6 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointee will be part of the dynamic Department of Respiratory Medicine based at the Cardiothoracic Centre alongside the Institute of Transplantation at the Freeman Hospital in Newcastle upon Tyne. This locum post provides an opportunity to be involved with the delivery of in- and out-patient respiratory care at Freeman Hospital, particularly lung cancer and also to support the in patient covid respiratory ward at the Royal Victoria Infirmary as Physician of the week on allocated weeks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an established lung cancer service with a strong lung cancer Multidisciplinary Team which the post-holder will join. They will have links throughout the range of specialist services at Freeman, particularly the Northern Centre for Cancer Care and the Department of Thoracic Surgery. In addition to the challenges and rewards of the role, we can offer you a commitment to teaching, education, research and audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The covid respiratory ward provides non invasive respiratory support for patients with covid infection, with the support of physiotherapists and specialist nurses. This can be for ITU step down patients or for patients for whom non invasive respiratory support is an appropriate ceiling of treatment. There is a team of medical junior doctors and a respiratory speciality trainee on the ward each week day plus junior medical doctors at the weekend, along with a consultant respiratory physician who will perform a ward round and lead the team daily for a week. This physician of the week role rotates amongst existing consultant staff for seven days at a time, between both RVI and Freeman Teams. Other respiratory duties are not expected in this week and there are no on call duties for Medicine as part of this cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for the post must be registered medical practitioners and on, or eligible to join, the Specialist Register within one month of the date of the Appointments Committee. Less than full time applications are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Newcastle upon Tyne Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is one of the most successful teaching NHS Trusts in the country. We have one of the highest number of specialist services of hospitals in the UK. With around 14,000 staff, the Newcastle Hospitals is one of the region’s major employers. We have a long-standing reputation for high quality clinical care with our staff’s commitment to excellence reflected in our consistent performance at the highest level. We are committed to being an “employer of choice” offering our staff superb benefits, looking after their wellbeing, and providing access to high-quality education, training, career progression and support which enables them to provide “healthcare at its very best – with a personal touch”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to promoting equality and diversity and recognise the benefit in providing an inclusive environment. We value and respect the diversity of our employees and aim to recruit a workforce which reflects the communities we serve, and is equipped to deliver the best service to our patients. We welcome all applications irrespective of people’s race, disability, gender, sexual orientation, religion or belief, age, gender identity, marriage and civil partnership, pregnancy and maternity and in particular those from under-represented groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion and further information regarding the opportunity and Directorate, please contact: &lt;strong&gt;Dr Ann Ward&lt;/strong&gt;, Lung cancer lead on 0191 233 6161 xt 37396, or via email at &lt;strong&gt;ann.ward14@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Dr Sophie West&lt;/strong&gt;, Head of Respiratory Department, 0191 233 6161 xt 37468 or &lt;strong&gt;sophie.west13@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this post, please visit NHS Jobs and complete the application form in full, please ensure that you provide references to cover the last 3 years. For any further queries, please contact &lt;strong&gt;Colin Sakhe, HR Advisor at&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Colin.Sakhe@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;, &lt;/strong&gt;quoting the post reference number.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NO AGENCIES PLEASE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to the rehabilitation of the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (Exceptions Order) 1975 and as such it will be necessary for a submission for Disclosure to be made to the Disclosure and Barring Services (formerly known as the Criminal Records Bureau) to check for any previous criminal convictions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note it is a requirement of The Newcastle upon Tyne Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust that all successful candidates who require a DBS for the post they have been offered pay for their DBS certificate. The method of payment is a salary deduction from your first month’s pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates who are shortlisted for interview will be contacted by e-mail, and may be required to complete psychometric tools in advance of the assessment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 13 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
